<img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-1764620 lazyload lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Master-P.jpeg" alt="" width="1280" height="853" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Master-P.jpeg 2000w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Master-P-897x598.jpeg 897w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Master-P-1728x1152.jpeg 1728w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Master-P-1536x1024.jpeg 1536w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Master-P-320x213.jpeg 320w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Master-P-640x427.jpeg 640w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Master-P-600x400.jpeg 600w" sizes="(max-width: 1280px) 100vw, 1280px" /> Master P has announced the death of his 29-year old daughter Tytyana Miller. The American rapper announced the death of his daughter, who he shared with ex Sonya C in an official statement. “Our family is dealing with an overwhelming grief for the loss of my daughter Tytyana,” Master P wrote on Instagram. “We respectfully request some privacy so that our family can grieve. We appreciate all of the prayers love and support.” He continued, “Mental illness & substance abuse is a real issue that we can’t be afraid to talk about. With God, we will get through this. #MyAngel.” His son Romeo Millie (Lil Romeo), also mourned the loss of his sister on Instagram. He wrote, “We appreciate all of the prayers, love, and support, and although this is sad times, I’m forever grateful for the memories I did have with my amazing sister.” “Love on your loved ones, life is short. The silver lining, I know she’s in a way better place and finally at peace and free. God Bless.”